msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-26-ai-skills-migration.adoc
msgid "Don't forget to configure the agent authentication mode using the API Key and/or subscription according to the provider before to launch it !"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-26-ai-skills-migration.adoc
msgid "Then ask the agent to start the migration using the following tailored prompt."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-26-ai-skills-migration.adoc
msgid "The prompt message already provide to AI important information like:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-26-ai-skills-migration.adoc
msgid "The text to be used to trigger the appropriate skill: \"Migrate this Spring Boot project to Quarkus\""
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-26-ai-skills-migration.adoc
msgid "The migration strategy to be used. See hereafter the section covering that part"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-26-ai-skills-migration.adoc
msgid "Migration and build instructions"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-26-ai-skills-migration.adoc
msgid "The summary report to be generated"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-26-ai-skills-migration.adoc
msgid "The https://github.com/quarkusio/skills/tree/main/skills/migrate-spring-to-quarkus[migrate-spring-to-quarkus] skill supports 2 migration strategies: full - Quarkus native or https://quarkus.io/guides/#q=spring[Spring Compatibility]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-26-ai-skills-migration.adoc
msgid "The `full` strategy implies that we want to migrate the code of Spring Boot using the Quarkus equivalents while the Spring Compatibility allows to reuse some of the Spring core features: DI, Web, Rest, Data, etc; annotations, etc."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _posts/2026-05-26-ai-skills-migration.adoc
msgid "The agent selects the correct installed skill by matching the phrase 'Migrate this Spring Boot' from the user's prompt with the skill's description."
msgstr ""

